SIMPLE: furious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Furious
<hw>Fu"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>furiosus</ets>, fr. <ets>furia</ets> rage, fury: cf. F.
<ets>furieux</ets>. See <er>Fury</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Transported with passion or fury; raging; violent; <as>as, a
furious animal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rushing with impetuosity; moving with violence;
<as>as, a <ex>furious</ex> stream; a <ex>furious</ex> wind or
storm.</as></def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impetuous; vehement; boisterous; fierce;
turbulent; tumultuous; angry; mad; frantic; frenzied.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fu"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fu"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>furiousness</ent>⟦br⟧
